Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
selectNet(25.10)                                              selectNet(25.10)

Name
       selectNet  - Selects a net and highlights it in the design display win-
       dow

Syntax
       selectNet

       [-help]

       {<netName> | {<list_of_netNames>} | -allDefClock  |  -clock  |  -nonDe-
       faultRule | -shield}

       Selects  a  net and highlights it in the design display window. You can
       use this command after importing or restoring the design.

Parameters
       -allDefClock
              Selects all nets that have a DEF attribute + USE CLOCK

              Note: The -allDefClock parameter is for  backward  compatibility
              only.  Cadence  recommends  that you use the -clock parameter to
              select all nets that have a DEF attribute + USE CLOCK

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -clock Selects all clock nets.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each selectNet parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man selectNet

       <netName> | {<list_of_netNames>}
              Specifies  the  name  of  one or more than one nets. You can use
              wildcards (*) to specify net names.

              Data_type: (net)*, optional

       -nonDefaultRule
              Selects all nets that have a DEF attribute

              + USE NONDEFAULTRULE

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -shield
              Selects all nets that have a DEF attribute

              + USE SHIELDNETS

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example:
              * The following command selects nets and highlights them in  the
                design display window:

                selectNet {net1 net2 net3}

Related Information
              * deselectNet

              * Floorplanning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

